45:59.942 --> 46:03.781
No matter what, I was to make
sure that you were on this ship.

46:03.847 --> 46:05.885
This was not the deal.

46:08.086 --> 46:11.651
Assist the Andromache to depart unmolested

46:11.724 --> 46:13.227
and you can remain with the girl

46:13.292 --> 46:15.891
and pick up the pieces
and explain yourself.

46:17.563 --> 46:21.362
Mr. Scott, you sided with
his daughter against him.

46:21.435 --> 46:23.666
You forgot your duty.

46:23.731 --> 46:26.065
You must have known there
would be consequences.

46:28.373 --> 46:32.216
But we men of duty must often
put our feelings aside...

46:33.385 --> 46:35.383
as you're about to witness.

46:48.297 --> 46:51.734
Do it.

46:57.673 --> 47:02.347
And this one?

47:30.481 --> 47:33.817
At the risk of overstepping my bounds,

47:33.889 --> 47:36.490
I think you should agree to
Captain Hornigold's terms.

47:38.590 --> 47:41.851
Lift the ban. What do you care about...

47:41.924 --> 47:43.524
They're beating her.

47:44.958 --> 47:46.294
She chose it.

47:46.359 --> 47:49.903
"She chose it"?

47:49.968 --> 47:53.240
"She chose it."

47:53.305 --> 47:55.179
I've been repeating those words to myself

47:55.244 --> 47:58.749
for well over a week now
and I find them wanting.

47:58.814 --> 48:01.854
Now he asks me to back off Charles,

48:01.919 --> 48:05.024
to proclaim to the world that
what happened to Max is acceptable,

48:05.089 --> 48:08.158
to apologize to those animals
for having ever said otherwise,

48:08.223 --> 48:10.228
and smile while they lord it over me.

48:10.293 --> 48:13.992
To make a dangerous situation
a lot less dangerous.

48:16.191 --> 48:18.325
Then convince me.

48:20.294 --> 48:23.331
Convince me that I should
betray her a second time...

48:25.069 --> 48:27.932
because that's what it
feels like I would be doing.

48:29.942 --> 48:33.007
Max chose.

48:33.080 --> 48:36.615
Why? I don't know.

48:36.680 --> 48:40.859
Maybe it was spite, maybe it was strength,

48:40.924 --> 48:43.394
maybe it was who the fuck knows what.

48:43.459 --> 48:45.887
To be perfectly honest, I don't care

48:45.960 --> 48:47.894
because the moment I start making choices

48:47.959 --> 48:49.759
based on her decisions,

48:49.824 --> 48:52.327
I've given her a hell of a
lot more power over my life

48:52.400 --> 48:55.135
than I am quite comfortable
ceding to a perfect stranger.

48:58.269 --> 49:00.365
Guilt is natural.

49:01.575 --> 49:05.908
It also goes away if you let it.

49:07.206 --> 49:10.245
Losing your life's work...

49:10.310 --> 49:12.779
that doesn't go away.

49:14.348 --> 49:16.886
No fucking longer!

49:18.119 --> 49:20.125
Captain?

49:20.190 --> 49:22.788
Charles?

49:22.861 --> 49:27.291
Do I understand correctly
that you've requested a skiff?

49:27.364 --> 49:29.467
I suppose that's none of my business,

49:29.532 --> 49:33.636
but you do realize that we
may be able to hunt again soon.

49:33.701 --> 49:36.037
What I'm hearing is all
second and thirdhand,

49:36.110 --> 49:39.775
but something is happening in that tavern.

49:40.849 --> 49:43.249
Our problem isn't in there.

49:43.314 --> 49:45.018
Never was.

49:49.228 --> 49:51.460
What the hell are you talking about?

49:51.525 --> 49:53.629
Chaz?

49:58.970 --> 50:00.935
Where are you going?

50:06.071 --> 50:07.502
Where is he?

50:07.575 --> 50:09.070
He's in a reinforced hold

50:09.142 --> 50:10.573
directly beneath us here.

50:10.638 --> 50:12.508
Forward end of the lower gundeck.

50:12.573 --> 50:16.212
Doors as thick as the
outer hull, as is the roof.

50:16.277 --> 50:18.213
Impossible to breach from here.

50:18.286 --> 50:21.179
He's also sitting right in
front of a powder magazine,

50:21.252 --> 50:23.251
so if we try to blow our way through,

50:23.316 --> 50:25.755
this whole ship is going down fast.

50:25.820 --> 50:27.322
Unless we can find a way in,

50:27.387 --> 50:29.424
there's no way to get
the guns off the boat.

50:29.489 --> 50:32.559
Anybody we send down there is
just gonna get cut to shreds.

50:32.624 --> 50:35.662
And we cannot sail.

50:35.727 --> 50:37.260
And we cannot sail.

50:38.957 --> 50:40.563
It doesn't make sense.

50:43.268 --> 50:45.236
If Bryson wants to force us to withdraw,

50:45.301 --> 50:48.203
what's to stop me from
burning the ship once we leave?

50:51.342 --> 50:53.477
We're missing something.

51:06.793 --> 51:08.496
There you are.

51:10.433 --> 51:12.570
Been looking all over for you.

51:12.635 --> 51:15.234
Thought I'd get a head start
going through Bryson's papers.

51:19.213 --> 51:21.445
Jameson.

51:21.510 --> 51:24.115
Beg your pardon?

51:24.180 --> 51:27.379
You said no man ever died
his first time over the side,

51:27.452 --> 51:30.254
but you forgot about Tom Jameson,

51:30.319 --> 51:33.293
boatswain's mate, about two years back.

51:33.359 --> 51:35.126
That's right.

51:35.191 --> 51:39.665
Also Christian Thoms,
Will Robbins, Jean DuBois,

51:39.738 --> 51:41.734
that Portuguese guy with the lisp...

51:41.799 --> 51:44.331
what was his name?

51:44.404 --> 51:46.571
That is funny.

51:46.636 --> 51:49.111
Thank you...

51:49.176 --> 51:50.605
for doing that.

51:53.042 --> 51:54.303
It helped.

52:04.151 --> 52:06.885
Miranda Barlow?

52:13.592 --> 52:15.158
Away from the hatch!

52:15.223 --> 52:16.959
Everyone!

52:35.689 --> 52:38.193
Captain Flint.

52:51.813 --> 52:55.814
He says, "I'm secure in the hold below."

53:02.256 --> 53:07.060
"With 20 of my men. I
can wait, but you cannot."

53:13.737 --> 53:16.304
"Before departing,"

53:16.376 --> 53:19.546
I sent a message to the
captain of the Scarborough.

53:19.611 --> 53:21.779
I told him where I was headed,

53:21.852 --> 53:24.850
"and I told him where he would find you."

53:24.915 --> 53:27.784
Sail to the east!

53:31.824 --> 53:33.825
Good God.

53:33.890 --> 53:35.794
The Scarborough!

53:39.097 --> 53:40.400
Look out!

